---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Pricing" description="Compare AGPL, Startup, Growth, and Enterprise commercial licensing for the Signal Protocol JavaScript SDK.">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h1>Choose the rights your product needs.</h1>
      <p class="lead">The complete SDK is available under AGPL. Proprietary products can purchase annual commercial production rights.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <article class="price-card"><p class="tier-label">Community</p><h3>AGPL</h3><p class="price"><strong>Free</strong></p><p class="price-description">For projects that can comply with AGPLv3.</p><ul><li>Complete SDK</li><li>Browser, Node, and Expo</li><li>Self-operated infrastructure</li><li>Community support</li></ul><a class="button button-secondary" href="/licensing">Understand AGPL use</a></article>
        <article class="price-card featured"><p class="tier-label">Startup</p><h3>Startup commercial license</h3><p class="price"><strong>$5,000</strong><span>/ year</span></p><p class="price-description">Commercial production rights for one named product owned by one legal entity.</p><ul><li>Licensed component: signal-protocol-js</li><li>Browser, Node, and Expo</li><li>SDK updates during the term</li><li>Self-service purchase</li></ul><a class="button" href="https://console.signal-protocol.dev/licenses/new?plan=startup">Purchase Startup</a></article>
        <article class="price-card"><p class="tier-label">Growth</p><h3>Growth commercial license</h3><p class="price"><strong>$20,000</strong><span>/ year</span></p><p class="price-description">Commercial rights with configurable product scope, implementation support, and services.</p><ul><li>Contract-defined component scope</li><li>Configurable product count</li><li>Integration support</li><li>Quote and signed order form</li></ul><a class="button button-secondary" href="https://console.signal-protocol.dev/contact?plan=growth">Schedule a meeting</a></article>
        <article class="price-card"><p class="tier-label">Enterprise / OEM</p><h3>Enterprise / OEM commercial license</h3><p class="price"><strong>$50,000+</strong><span>/ year</span></p><p class="price-description">Negotiated product portfolio, redistribution, security, and support terms.</p><ul><li>Contract-defined component scope</li><li>Portfolio or OEM rights</li><li>Security review and SLA</li><li>MSA or signed order form</li></ul><a class="button button-secondary" href="https://console.signal-protocol.dev/contact?plan=enterprise">Schedule a meeting</a></article>
      </div>
      <p class="pricing-note">Taxes may apply. The current Startup profile licenses signal-protocol-js; any broader component scope must be explicit in the signed agreement. The final agreement controls the grant, covered products, support, renewal, and post-expiration rights.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-subtle">
    <div class="container split-grid">
      <article class="split-card"><p class="eyebrow">Startup checkout</p><h2>Designed for self-service.</h2><p>Sign in, name the legal entity and covered product, accept the commercial terms, and complete annual checkout through Stripe.</p></article>
      <article class="split-card"><p class="eyebrow">Growth and Enterprise</p><h2>Scope before purchase.</h2><p>Integration support, portfolio rights, redistribution, security review, and service levels require a short meeting and signed order form.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
